import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['daily_return'] = pd.to_numeric(data['daily_return'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='daily_return', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['daily_return'].mean(), color='red', label='mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['daily_return'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['daily_return'].median(), color='green', label='median: {:.2f}'.format(data['daily_return'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='volume', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average daily volume of stocks traded?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['volume'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['volume'].mean():,.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='adjclose', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend in the adjusted closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
